# Phase Development Rules
- Never implement future phases early.
- Determine the active phase from documentation or the user instruction before changing code.
- Complete one phase fully before moving to the next.
- Before declaring a phase complete, run the relevant build, typecheck, lint, and test commands.
- Stop after phase completion, report results, and wait for the next instruction.
- Never continue with unresolved errors, skipped verification, or failing checks.
- If phase scope is unclear, state the ambiguity and ask before expanding scope.
